> I have been trying to get my new computer to power off on 
> shutdown, but no
> luck.  The kernel says it's powering down but it doesn't.  
> Instead I get
> [<c########>] where the #'s are seemingly random hex numbers printed
> repeated over and over.  It finally stops after many 
> screenfuls of this
> and eventually reboots.  I applied the recent APM patch to 
> 2.2.9 and still
> no luck.  System is RedHat 6.0 with a custom 2.2.9 kernel (fresh, not
> patched against redhat's).  The motherboard is a Gigabyte GA-6BXE w/
> Intel 440BX AGPset.  The config file follows.
